def: The act of riding steeple chases.
Consisting of, or resembling, pituite or mucus; full of mucus;discharging mucus. Pituitous fever (Med.), typhoid fever; entericfever.

Having the head, thorax, and abdomen separated by a deepconstriction. Disjunct tetrachords (Mus.), tetrachords so disposed toeach other that the gravest note of the upper is one note higher thanthe acutest note of the other.
A fixed star of the second magnitude, in the constellationGemini. Cf. 3d Castor.
The ninth month of the year, containing thurty days.
Capable of being insulted or affronted. [R.] Emerson.
A kind of worsted braid, about an inch broad. [Scot.] Jamieson.
